  "texts": [
    "Thiazine dyes, which are often used in the textile industry and can be harmful to the environment, can be effectively removed through photocatalysis using TiO 2 -based systems.",
    "Studies have focused on the degradation of methylene blue, rhodamine B, and other thiazine dyes (Vara and Ortiz, 2016; Acar et al., 2015).",
    "Researchers have investigated the optimal conditions for photocatalytic water treatment, including dye concentration, pH, and TiO 2 catalyst loading.",
    "The process not only degrades the dyes Efficient photocatalytic degradation of organic dyes by Silver nanaoparticles/TiO 2 /Ti 3 C 2 T x MXene composites under UV and visible light (Othman et al., 2021).",
    "but can also lead to the formation of less harmful or non-toxic intermediates."
  ],
